						               													<description>&amp;quot;The Book Game&amp;quot; consists of 4000 questions and answers (1000 designed especially for children) taken from &amp;quot;The Book&amp;quot; (a version of the Bible).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A &amp;quot;Question &amp;amp; Answer&amp;quot; game (ala Trivial Pursuit).  Correctly answer a question and advance your pawn one space. Be the first to reach the &amp;quot;Finish&amp;quot; space by advancing your pawn seven spaces.  On your turn, instead of answering a question to advance your pawn, you may choose to &amp;quot;block&amp;quot; an opponent by correctly answering a question.  Blocks are removed by correctly answering questions.  Advancement only occurs if a pawn is not &amp;quot;blocked.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Questions are divided into two sets: The Old and New Testaments.  A die roll (50-50 chance) determines which set of questions a question is drawn from on your turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
